			<h3>Entry Requirements</h3>
				<p>It is preferred to complete NEBOSH International General Certificate or equivalent to Level 3 before undertaking the NEBOSH International Diploma.<br /><br />
				Fresher’s - Core Engineering graduates, Science graduates & polytechnic diploma holders with NEBOSH General Certificate or equivalent to Level 3.<br /><br />
				Good standard of written English communication is required since the examinations are held in English.<br /></p>
			</li>
			<li>
				<h3>Course Syllabus</h3>
				<p>NEBOSH International Diploma is divided into four units, each of which is assessed separately:<br /><br />
					Unit IA: International management of health and safety<br /><br />
					Unit IB: International control of hazardous agents in the workplace<br /><br />
					Unit IC: International workplace and work equipment safety<br /><br />
					Unit ID: International application of health and safety theory and practice<br /><br />
					<b>Unit IA: International management of health and safety</b><br /><br />
					&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Principles of Health & Safety Management<br />
					&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Loss causation &amp; Incident Investigation<br />
					&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Identifying Hazards, Assessing & Evaluating Risk<br />
					&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Risk Control &amp; Emerging Planning<br />
					&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Organizational Factors<br />
					&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Human Factors<br />
					&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Regulating Health &amp; Safety<br />
					&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Measuring Health &amp; Safety performance<br /><br />
					
					<b>Unit IB: International Management of Hazardous Agents in the Workplace</b><br /><br />
					&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Principles of Toxicology and Epidemiology<br />
					&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Hazardous Substances and Other Chemicals - Assessment of Risk<br />
					&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Hazardous Substances and Other Chemicals - Engineering Controls and Personal Protective Equipment<br />
					&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Monitoring and Measuring<br />
					&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Biological Agents<br />
					&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Physical Agents 1 – Noise &amp; Vibration<br />
					&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Physical Agents 2 – Radiation <br />
					&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Psycho – Social Agents<br />
					&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Musculoskeletal Risks and Controls<br />
					&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Work Environment Risks and Controls<br />
					&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Managing Occupational Health<br />
					<br />
					
					<b>Unit IC: International workplace and work equipment safety</b><br /><br />
